    - target: {fileID: 1651618891599351730, guid: 93cac7b193b5c894e90059f8b3324b28, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "Dog anatomy refers to the structure of a dog\u2019s body, including
        its external features and internal systems. Externally, it includes parts
        like the head, ears, legs, tail, and coat. Internally, a dog\u2019s body
        is made up of systems such as the skeletal system (bones for support), muscular
        system (movement), circulatory system (heart and blood flow), respiratory
        system (lungs for breathing), digestive system (processing food), and nervous
        system (brain and nerves for control)."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
